1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: Two new paramedics are in at the deep end, treating a man with life-threatening injuries and a victim of three epileptic fits.

2.title: Episode #2.2
2.plot: Paramedics tend to a patient with a severe allergic reaction while at the same time a man has fallen unconscious after a severe diabetic attack.

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: A woman has collapsed in the snow. A 61-year-old man has fallen on ice. And a pregnant woman's waters have broken early.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: Paramedics rush to aid a grandmother with osteoporosis who fell down the stairs carrying her grandson. And an elderly man is found unconscious face down in his hallway.

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: The West Midlands is hit by the worst snowstorm in years. Crews battle the elements to treat a woman semi-conscious in police custody and to attend a suspected miscarriage.

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Paramedics rush to treat a diabetic woman involved in a car crash, while an 82-year-old with breathing difficulties is close to death and a man suffers chest pains at work.

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: A suspected drink driver crashes into a lamp post, crews rush to a man with a dangerously high heart rate, and a two year old has a severe allergic reaction.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: Paramedics rush to a 10-year-old boy suffering a major epileptic fit. An elderly woman struggles to breathe. And paramedics are called to a man with extreme anxiety.

9.title: Episode #2.9
9.plot: A crew need to revive a man slipping close to a diabetic coma. An elderly woman is in severe pain after falling on the ice. There's also an abusive regular caller, and a fitting baby.

10.title: Episode #2.10
10.plot: A drunk driver crashes her car, an elderly war veteran falls at home, and a four-year-old is drifting in and out of consciousness with dangerously low sugar levels.

1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Paramedic chelsie and technician simon rush to save a baby born not breathing. In birmingham, paramedics jo and peter treat a five-year-old having an asthma attack.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: The ambulance crews treat a 17-year-old rugby player with a suspected bleed on the brain, an eight-month-old baby who's choking, and a man who's trapped in his car.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: The paramedics are called out to a cyclist crushed by a lorry. They also help a man who's fallen from a barge and rush to find a baby in cardiac arrest.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Paramedics fight to save a man whose heart has stopped for 50 minutes. And a 15-year-old boy is found unconscious in a park after drinking two litres of whisky.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: A 71-year-old man is left with a broken ankle when he is knocked off his bike by a dog. And the paramedics help a man who's been trapped for over 20 hours with a broken leg.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Paramedic rob and student paramedic ally are called to a custody suite in birmingham to deal with a prisoner who is aggressive and abusive but may have overdosed on heroin.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: The paramedics treat an aggressive patient. A pregnant mum is worried about the impact of a car crash. And a man with dementia gets a lift to the hospital.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: In warwickshire, a 19-year-old man has fallen from a horse and the horse has fallen on top of him. In birmingham, a man wants to do a poo in the back of the ambulance.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: An 89-year-old woman refuses to go to hospital despite her vomiting. And a 93-year-old war veteran desperately needs medical attention for a sepsis that could kill him.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: The paramedics must lift a man with a seriously damaged neck. One false move could mean he will never walk again. And a man has chest pains after being involved in a hit and run.

imdb.title: 999: on the frontline
plot: Filmed simultaneously with ambulance crews across the west midlands, this series shows in real time the range of cases paramedics attend to.
